                    ## Join Me

                    I am actively seeking enthusiastic students to become part of my research lab --- the **P**rogramming, **E**ducation, **a**nd **C**omputer-**H**uman Interaction Lab (PEACH Lab). 
                    Candidates with strong competencies in fields such as human-computer interaction, educational technology, and software engineering are highly preferred.

                    ### Application Materials

                    Before making contact, kindly review the research projects listed on my website to ensure that your research interests align with ours. Please note that due to the volume of inquiries, we may not be able to respond to each email. Prospective candidates are encouraged to [contact me](mailto:april.wang@inf.ethz.ch?subject=Prospective-Student) directly with the following details:

                    - Your CV
                    - A brief paragraph outlining your background (e.g., skills in design and programming, reasons for wanting to join the lab)
                    - A brief paragraph detailing your research interests (e.g., any previous research experience, and how your interests coincide with our work)
                    - Examples of your publications or writing samples (optional)
                    - The names and contacts of two references for your application (optional)

                    ### PhD Positions
                    
                    #### Direct Doctorate PhD Positions (for bachelor graduates)
                    ETH Zurich's Department of Computer Science provides a [Direct Doctorate PhD Program](https://inf.ethz.ch/doctorate/direct-doctorate-computer-science.html), designed for extraordinary undergraduate applicants. We encourage you to reach out before applying via the Direct Doctorate admissions portal.
                    
                    Please note, applications for the Direct Doctorate will be accepted from November 15 to December 15, 2023.                    

                    #### PhD Positions (for master graduates)
                    If you're a strong candidate who has already completed a master's degree, or you're about to, we invite you to get in touch directly. 
                    
                    Given that ETH does not limit the enrollment periods for PhD students, we can be flexible with the starting dates.

                    #### PhD Fellowships
                    Stay tuned for more details!

                    ### Postdoc Positions
                    We invite highly qualified postdoctoral candidates to become part of our lab. We are particularly interested in those who focus on developing collaborative and educational programming tools. We anticipate that the successful candidates will aim to publish their research in academic communities such as CHI, CSCW, L@S, AIED or other related platforms. Please feel free to reach out to us directly. We also provide support for Postdoc applicants when applying for the [ETH Zurich Postdoctoral Fellowship](https://ai.ethz.ch/education/phd-and-postdoc-programs/postdoc-fellowships.html).

                    ### Undergraduate and Master Students at ETH Zurich 
                    I'm thrilled to collaborate with undergraduates and master students at ETH Zurich who have an interest in the type of research I conduct. Many of the students I've worked with have gone on to co-author papers with me, and a significant number are now enrolled in prestigious graduate schools or working in leading industries. There's often an opportunity for students who have experience or interest in areas like software development, data science, or UX research to join in on projects.

                    ### Research Internship
                    Students who are interested in joining my lab for a summer research internship may take a look at the following fellowship: 

                    - [ETH SSRF](https://inf.ethz.ch/studies/summer-research-fellowship.html) is a two-month summer internship program open to all undergraduate and graduate students worldwide.
                    - [ThinkSwiss](https://thinkswiss.org/research-scholarship/) is a three-months summer research scholarship open to undergraduate and graduate students who are currently enrolled in a U.S. or Canadian university. 

                    ## About ETH Zurich
                    ETH Zurich is one of the leading international universities for technology and the natural sciences. 
                    It is well-known for its excellent education, ground-breaking fundamental research and for putting its new findings directly into practice. 
                    It offers researchers an inspiring working environment and its students a comprehensive education.
                    
